This is a great DVD.  My Great Nephew has all the George DVDs and this one by far is his favorite.  He likes to watch it before he goes to bed.  I love that you really do learn a lot from these DVDs as well.  I would recommend these DVDs to anyone with young children.

My children absolutely LOVE Curious George.  I love that it is educational as well as fun, even if the theme song is a bit annoying after a while.  They, my 2 and 3 year olds, never get tired of watching the episodes.  I never tire of the quality shows that are being produced.

Here are the episodes on this DVD:

Night of the Wiener Dog
Movie House Monkey
Say Goodnight, George
Hundley's Great Escape
The Big Sleepy
Red Sky at Night, Monkey's Delight
Curious George and the Invisible Sound
Water to Ducks

My grandson loves Curious George. He has watched him since he was able to watch TV and still watches him today and he is now six. We had all the dvd's except this one. Now we have them all.
Curious George is great for the kids. One of the best cartoons around today.

Includes Episodes: 'Night Of The Wiener Dog'; 'Movie House Monkey'; 'Say Goodnight, George'; 'Hundley's Great Escape'; 'The Big Sleepy'; 'Red Sky At Night, Monkey's Delight'; 'Curious George And The Invisible Sound' and 'Water To Ducks'.

George is loveable and while his intention is good, it may require more thought. Eight full episodes in this DVD.  Guidance and supervision from the man in the yellow hat isn't usually available until after all the trouble!  A lesson he never seems to learn.... monkeys and children need attention and supervision. :-D

I am so sick of the programming on Disney Channel teaching my boy that if you want to get down from a tree you need a giant piece of celery to slide down.  We try and give our child other things to do, but the reality is that sometimes it is just more appropriate to let him watch some TV...if you can stand the agenda of the people making the programs.

Then we ran across Curious George and were relieved.  No agendas, no politically correct subject matter, no illogical logic.  The first time we watched one it was like taking your shoes off after a long walk on a summer day...aaahhhh.

To top it off, each DVD only costs around $10. I ended up buying 10 different titles and have been happy with every one...thus I will copy and paste this review on each one of them.

We watch Curious George on tv every morning.  On road trips she would ask to watch him,but we didn't have any videos of him.  When I found the Curious George videos on Amazon, it was like striking gold.  These videos contain multiple episodes totally 90 minutes of enjoyment.  She loves them and it occupies her.

I think I might enjoy watching the Curious George episodes as much as my 3 year old, it's on netflix instant play & we've watched them all more than once; My daughter never grows sick of them & I always enjoy a good laugh with the New England humor. I also love the fact that there's no negativity of any kind in the show. No bad guys, no scary parts, no negative words like "stupid" or "idiot" like so many of the other cartoons these days. They are also educational with real-life skills such as composting, recycling & gardening,ect. to name a few. We started buying them individually for long treks across county in the car & they prove to be a perfect entertainer for our daughter & also perfect length so I know she's not gonna spend too much time in front of the screen. I happened to stumble upon a few discs at Target one day; so I decided to get on Amazon & see if I could get a box set for cheaper but in fact it is more expensive through Amazon. Plus, the individual discs on Amazon are even more expensive than buying them through Target or Walmart. You can buy most disc's for $5 at Target & Walmart. There's a few that range from $6 to $10 for whatever reason, yet those prices for those specific discs are still more affordable than Amazon surprisingly enough.
You can't go wrong with Curious George... great dvd that the kids will sit & watch & lasts long enough for mom to enjoy the quiet time too! :)

The informative reviews helped me to choose this DVD, which is now my 3 year old's absolute favorite.  My toddler is autistic, so it isn't always easy to find quality, educational programming, which also holds his attention.  I had hoped this video would help with the bedtime routine but, if I let him, he would watch it around the clock!  He actually laughs hysterically at certain scenes, every time.  The cartoons are relaxing to watch, the soft colors and animation so closely resemble the classic book illustrations.  We enjoy the clips of the children, throughout the programs.  I remember Curious George from my own childhood, and we will definitely be adding more of the DVD's, very soon!
